                 code. A heuristic design similarity measure is defined,
                 based on the Parnas' information hiding principle. The
                 measure supports two services: clustering, which
                 identifies groups of related procedures, and maverick
                 analysis, which identifies individual procedures that
                 appear to be in the wrong module. The tool has already
                 provided useful advice in several real programming
                 projects. The tool will soon incorporate an automatic
                 tuning method, which allows the tool to learn from its
                 mistakes, adapting its advice to the architect's
                 preferences. A preliminary experiment demonstrates that
                 the automatically tuned similarity function can assign
                 procedures to modules very accurately."
}

